ðŸ’± Currency Exchange Program in Java
This is a simple Java console application that converts a given amount in Indian Rupees (INR) to one of the following currencies:

USD (United States Dollar)

WON (South Korean Won)

EURO (Euro)

The user is prompted to enter the amount in INR and select a target currency. The program then calculates and displays the converted amount using fixed conversion rates.

ðŸ”§ Features:
User input with Scanner

Menu-driven interface

Currency conversion using switch statement

Handles invalid choices and negative amounts

ðŸš€ How to Run:
Compile the code using javac CurrencyExchange.java

Run with java CurrencyExchange

Follow the prompts in the console
